 Executive Report

A simulated Samba exploitation attack was conducted using Metasploit against a vulnerable system. Detection was successfully performed by Wazuh, triggering a high-priority alert. Correlation and threat intelligence enrichment confirmed malicious intent. The SOC team executed containment by isolating the compromised system and blocking the attacker’s IP using CrowdSec. Evidence was collected following proper chain-of-custody procedures. No business impact or data exfiltration was detected. Recommendations include patching vulnerable services, continuous monitoring, credential hardening, and regular SOC simulations to maintain preparedness.

